                <div class="feature-box">
                    <h3>Can a wife get khula without her husband's consent?</h3>
                    <p>Yes. Khula is a wife's right, and she can file for it in the Family Court even if her husband does not agree. The court can grant khula so a woman is not trapped in a marriage she wants to end. We handle the whole process with care and confidentiality, and we'll explain each step for your situation.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-box">
                    <h3>Who gets child custody after divorce?</h3>
                    <p>The Family Court decides custody based on the welfare of the child, not just the wishes of either parent. Mothers often receive custody of young children, while the father usually keeps a right to maintenance and visitation. Every case is different, so we look at your family's facts and advise you honestly.</p>
                </div>
